                  // æ³¨æ„ï¼šè¿™é‡Œéœ€è¦æ¯æ¬¡å®ä¾‹åŒ– Enigoï¼Œå¼€é”€å¯èƒ½ç•¥å¤§ï¼Œä½†å¯¹äºæ‰‹åŠ¨ç‚¹å‡»é¢‘ç‡æ˜¯å¯ä»¥æ¥å—çš„
                  if let Ok(mut enigo) = Enigo::new(&Settings::default()) {
                      if let Ok((x, y)) = enigo::Mouse::location(&enigo) {
                          if let Ok(mut pos) = LAST_CLICK_POS.lock() {
                              *pos = (x, y);
                          }
                      }
                  }
             }
        }) {
            error!("Error: {:?}", error);
        }
    });

    tauri::Builder::default()
        .plugin(tauri_plugin_single_instance::init(|_app, _args, _cwd| {
            info!("æ£€æµ‹åˆ°ç¬¬äºŒä¸ªå®ä¾‹å¯åŠ¨ï¼Œå·²é˜»æ­¢");
        }))
        .plugin(tauri_plugin_opener::init())
        .plugin(tauri_plugin_global_shortcut::Builder::new().build())
        .plugin(tauri_plugin_clipboard_manager::init())
        .plugin(tauri_plugin_store::Builder::default().build())
        .setup(|app| {
            // Load settings into cache on startup
            let app_handle = app.handle().clone();
            tauri::async_runtime::spawn(async move {
                match get_settings(app_handle.clone()).await {
                    Ok(settings) => {
                        info!("Settings loaded: {:?}", settings);

                        // Register custom shortcut
                        if let Err(e) = update_shortcut(app_handle.clone(), settings.shortcut.clone()).await {
                            error!("Failed to register shortcut: {}, falling back to Ctrl+Q", e);
                            let _ = update_shortcut(app_handle.clone(), "Ctrl+Q".to_string()).await;
                        }

                        // Check if first run and API key is empty
                        if settings.first_run && settings.api_key.is_empty() {
                            info!("First run detected, showing settings window");
                            let _ = open_settings_window(app_handle.clone()).await;
                        }
                    }
                    Err(e) => {
                        error!("Failed to load settings: {}", e);
                    }
                }
            });

            // Create menu items
            let settings_item = MenuItem::with_id(app, "settings", "è®¾ç½®", true, None::<&str>)?;
            let quit = MenuItem::with_id(app, "quit", "é€€å‡ºç¨‹åº", true, None::<&str>)?;
            let menu = Menu::with_items(app, &[&settings_item, &quit])?;

            // ä½¿ç”¨åº”ç”¨å›¾æ ‡åˆ›å»ºç³»ç»Ÿæ‰˜ç›˜
            let tray_icon = if let Some(icon) = app.default_window_icon() {
                icon.clone()
            } else {
                // å¦‚æœæ²¡æœ‰é»˜è®¤å›¾æ ‡ï¼Œå°è¯•ä»æ–‡ä»¶åŠ è½½
                warn!("No default window icon found, using fallback");
                app.default_window_icon().unwrap().clone()
            };

            TrayIconBuilder::new()
                .icon(tray_icon)
                .menu(&menu)
                .on_menu_event(|app, event| {
                    match event.id.as_ref() {
                        "settings" => {
                            let app_handle = app.clone();
                            tauri::async_runtime::spawn(async move {
                                let _ = open_settings_window(app_handle).await;
                            });
                        }
                        "quit" => {
                            app.exit(0);
                        }
                        _ => {}
                    }
                })
                .build(app)?;

            if let Some(window) = app.get_webview_window("main") {
                let _ = window.hide();
            }

            Ok(())
        })
        .invoke_handler(tauri::generate_handler![
            translate,
            get_mouse_position,
            get_settings,
            save_settings,
            validate_api_key,
            validate_shortcut,
            update_shortcut,
            open_settings_window
        ])
        .run(tauri::generate_context!())
        .expect("error while running tauri application");
}

